<TEXT>
an army soldier who had served in the 
persian gulf and three other men have been arrested in the theft of 
a huge cache of military weapons and explosives federal and local 
officials said saturday 
the materiel seized friday and saturday from a warehouse and one 
suspects home in jacksonville included enough military explosives 
to destroy an entire city block said willi ellison agent in 
charge of the federal bureau of alcohol tobacco and firearms in 
jacksonville 
michael tubbs a us army special forces sergeant had been 
brought back from operation desert shield in saudi arabia within 
the past several weeks ellison said tubbs was already facing 
possible federal firearms and explosives charges in connection with 
a january 1987 incident at fort bragg nc in which two soldiers 
were jumped and tied to a tree by two masked men who stole their 
rifles 
he remained restricted saturday to the base at fort campbell 
ky ellison said 
another soldier army warrant officer jeffrey jennett has 
already been arrested and charged for the 1987 incident jennett 
was arrested in charleston sc on thursday night and charged in 
federal court with assault with intent to commit felony theft and 
with stealing an m16 rifle ellison said 
also seized friday and saturday were military weapons manuals 
magazines describing how to wage urban warfare and make homemade 
bombs and hate materials including videotapes of speeches by adolf 
hitler ellison said 
all the literature focused on just a litany of hate against 
jews blacks and other minorities ellison said they were 
wellequipped to engage in major warfare 
our preliminary indications are that these individuals are 
related to the kkk and the aryan nation added john gordon deputy 
director of police operations at the jacksonville sheriffs office 
arrested in jacksonville on friday were michael tubbs brother 
john and stephen fussell a 26yearold handyman both men face 
federal firearms and conspiracy charges 
the seizures and arrests resulted from a multistate 
investigation by federal and local agencies focusing on the theft 
of weapons and explosives from military installations ellison 
said 
this investigation spans several states ellison said 
were talking about tennessee kentucky north carolina and 
jacksonville 
much of the firearms and explosives are believed to have been 
stolen from us army posts at fort bragg and fort campbell 
ellison said 
the arsenal recovered at john tubbs home and a miniwarehouse 
included soviet ar15 and us m16 automatic rifles thousands of 
rounds of ammunition an antiaircraft machine gun antipersonnel 
land mines numerous handguns and shotguns a 40mm grenade 
launcher hand grenades smoke grenades tear gas dynamite 
blasting caps booby traps and other highexplosives 
ellison and gordon wouldnt comment on any possible motives the 
four men had for stockpiling such destructive material 
the investigation is still continuing and there may be more 
arrests in the future ellison said 
