<TEXT>
nato and warsaw pact negotiators sunday 
initialed a landmark treaty to slash nonnuclear weapons across 
europe 
the initialling approves the text of the conventional forces in 
europe treaty scheduled to be signed monday in paris by president 
bush soviet president mikhail gorbachev and representatives of 20 
other nations in the two alliances 
the leaders will be in paris for a 34nation summit of the 
conference on security and cooperation in europe 
the treaty billed as the pact that formally ends the cold war 
limits each alliance to 20000 main battle tanks 30000 armored 
combat vehicles 20000 artillery pieces 6800 fighter planes and 
2000 combat helicopters 
the 70page accord also regulates troops movements and permits 
mutual inspections 
negotiators late saturday finalized another document that 
pledges a regular exchange of information on troop levels arms 
systems and deployment and military budgets austrias national 
news agency apa reported 
the pact is also scheduled to be signed monday 
the two documents were worked out after 20 months of 
negotiations 
negotiators originally sought a deal on troop reductions but 
agreed to suspend the talks so the treaty could be ready for 
signing in paris 
delegates plan to reconvene in vienna nov 29 to discuss 
military personnel cuts 
hungarian officials said thursday the warsaw pact down to six 
members after german unification would cease to function as a 
military alliance by july 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

