we hope that something will change in the next couple of weeks to 
alter that assessment he spent the last week meeting with 
european officials to seek a farm subsidies agreement officials 
had hoped to resolve the issue in time for global trade talks 
scheduled to open in brussels belgium on dec 3 
the united states and other big farm exporters like argentina 
want the agriculture agreement to include 75 percent cuts in 
subsidies and 90 percent cuts in customs tariffs 
the 12member european community including france and germany 
has offered to agree to a 30 percent cut in farm subsidies over 10 
years sweden and other european countries that are not members of 
the ec have agreed to subsidy cuts of up to 50 percent 
the global trade talks known as the uruguay round for the 
country where they were launched in 1986 involve 105 nations 
us trade representative carla hills warned thursday that a 
failure of the trade talks in belgium would increase tensions among 
trading partners and could frustrate international cooperation on 
issues ranging from the gulf crisis to the environment 
the bush administration has a lot riding on the trade agreement 
us officials believe that removing trade barriers is the best 
hope for lowering huge us trade deficits by expanding overseas 
sales 
farmers in europe have staged noisy protests in recent weeks to 
assure their governments do not buckle under to pressure to lower 
farm subsidies 
