<TEXT>
it has been more than 25 years since zero mostel 
first trudged across the stage of the imperial theater as tevye the 
philosophical milkman in fiddler on the roof 
there have been a lot of tevyes since then from herschel 
bernardi to jan peerce but the role has been coopted in recent 
years by topol the israeliborn actor who starred in the london 
production of the musical as well as the movie version 
now after a long national tour topol has arrived on broadway 
where fiddler opened sunday at the gershwin theater its no 
surprise to report that star and show both hold up well in fact 
this is a glorious revival with topol delivering a genuine star 
turn and the material hasnt grown old at all 
fiddler on the roof was the last great musical in the 
rodgers and hammerstein tradition a style ramph developed and 
perfected in the 1940s with such classic shows as oklahoma 
carousel and south pacific 
fiddler which originally opened in new york in september 
1964 has that same extraordinary integration of story and song 
there is not a wasted moment in the musical 
songs music by jerry bock and lyrics by sheldon harnick are 
used to explain character or advance plot the story which joseph 
stein artfully adapted from the stories of sholom aleichem serves 
as a framework for those musical numbers and everything was tied 
together perfectly by jerome robbins whose original direction and 
choreography have been faithfully reproduced here by ruth mitchell 
and sammy dallas bayes 
there quite simply isnt a better opening scene in the american 
musical theater in that one song tradition the musicals 
underlying theme the ties that bind together the small jewish 
community in the turnofthecentury russian village of anatevka 
are brilliantly stated 
the story of how those ties start to unravel torn apart by 
personal social and political upheavals are brilliantly 
delineated by bock harnick stein and especially robbins 
topols tevye is more aristocratic than mostels milkman he has 
a commanding voice full and deep and he moves with an authority 
that makes the eventual destruction of his world and the dispersal 
of his family especially poignant yet topol doesnt miss a moment 
of the shows humor never forgetting the mans indecisiveness 
whether he is arguing with his wife or with god 
the dances remain firstrate particularly teyves dream 
sequence in which motel the tailor is chosen as the husband for his 
oldest daughter 
marcia lewis makes a wonderful golde shrewish yet ultimately 
sympathetic there are some sharp cameos particularly ruth jaroslow 
as the busybody matchmaker mark zeller as the butcher lazar wolf 
and tia riebling as the sweetvoiced hodel 
boris aronsons original designs with their echoes of marc 
chagall paintings remain as evocative as ever particularly 
teyves house which spins around the large stage and opens 
gracefully to reveal its homespun interior to the audience 
at one of the final preview performances the audience was swept 
up into the show as soon as the curtain rose many of them began 
humming along with the score they knew what to expect and this 
revival delivers it 
the one surprise may be that this fiddler on the roof turns 
out to be as good as they remember the musical to be 
