whether its handling complaints from irate 
shoppers or pampering hotel guests customer service has become a 
top priority for most american executives according to a poll 
released sunday 
about half the customers have noticed according to the poll 
the poll commissioned by john hancock financial services and 
conducted by louis harris and associates inc surveyed both 
consumers and senior executives from serviceoriented businesses 
such as retailers utilities and financial services companies 
the poll found the vast majority of executives placed a premium 
on quality customer service but 50 percent of the consumers said 
service is improving 
that number was the highest it has been in the 19 years the 
harris group has surveyed attitudes on service 
fortyfive percent of the customers polled however still feel 
quality is declining moreover 51 percent reported declining 
personal attention from service providers and 60 percent perceived 
declining value for the money they spend 
